text:
+ Newly renovated halal coffeeshop.

+ Has a good range of stalls including: Thai BBQ, Melaka Claypot, Nasi Ayam chicken rice, Indian Muslim, Noodles, HKM/CKT Hawkerman, Nasi Lemak, and Tenderbest Chicken.

- Prices higher than normal for a coffeeshop, e.g. $4.80 for fishball noodles.

- No nearby sheltered MSCP.

Kedaikopi has been our favorite spot for dinner.

Recently hawkermann introduce new menu and i had tried their chai poh kuay teow.

So sedap with the sambal belacan.. fuyoohh.. coz i love chai poh n fried kuay teow.  So this is a good combi..

Super nice nasi Lemak, seriously better than famous ones. Very fragrant rice and crispy well marinated fried chicken wing or drumstick. The sambal chilli is also the thumbs up. Must try!

Teh peng is also nicely done or rather they make nice drinks like ice holick, ice milo too. Not too sweet, not too bland.
The asam pedas not even taste of asam pedas plus the fish is so smell of the pungent when keep it too long. $8.50 with this kind of food not recommendations to others.

I recently discovered that the "Mee Bagus" coffee shop, despite being listed as open until 10:30 PM on Google, actually closes its doors around 8:00+PM. It's unclear whether this is an official early closure or if the staff simply choose to wrap up operations ahead of schedule. Hopefully, the shop will consider extending its hours to accommodate local residents who would love to enjoy their delicious "Mee Bagus" later in the evening.
